cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CC

This paper discusses the use of neural network models for a linguistic task, specifically the English past tense. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of modern encoder-decoder models, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the flaws and limitations of these models, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
